## Karpathy LLM Coding Guidelines
# Source: https://github.com/forrestchang/andrej-karpathy-skills

### Think Before Coding
- Don't assume. Surface tradeoffs and multiple interpretations before picking one.
- If unclear, stop and ask — don't guess silently.
- Push back when a simpler approach exists.

### Simplicity First
- Minimum code for the problem. No speculative features, no unrequested abstractions.
- Ask: "Would a senior engineer say this is overcomplicated?" If yes, simplify.

### Surgical Changes
- Only touch what the request requires. Don't improve adjacent code.
- Match existing project style. Remove only YOUR orphaned imports/vars.
- Every changed line must trace to the user's request.

### Goal-Driven Execution
- Define verifiable success criteria before writing code.
- For multi-step tasks: `[Step] → verify: [check]`
- Ask clarifying questions BEFORE, not after mistakes.
